  "Name": "Accounts with altSecurityIdentities configured",
  "ScriptName": "altSecurityIdentitiesConfigured",
  "ShortName": "SI000102",
  "Description": "It is possible to add values to the altSecurityIdentities attribute and essentially impersonate that account. The altSecurityIdentities attribute is a multi-valued attribute used to create mappings for X.509 certificates and external Kerberos accounts. This indicator checks for accounts with the altSecurityIdentities attribute configured.",
  "CategoryId": "5",
  "Weight": 7,
  "Severity": "Warning",
  "Schedule": "1d",
  "Impact": 7,
  "LikelihoodOfCompromise": "<p>This type of attack may be easy to spot as it is rarely configured during normal operations. However, it is possible for this attribute to be configured genuinely.</p>\n      <h3>References</h3>\n      <p><a href=\"https://www.cert.ssi.gouv.fr/uploads/ad_checklist.html#vuln_delegation_a2d2\" target=\"_blank\">Constrained authentication delegation to a domain controller service | ANSSI</a></p>",
